%div{"data-role" => "page"}
  %div{"data-role" => "header"}
    %h1 .removeAttr()
  #removeAttr1{"data-role" => "content", "data-theme" => "c"}
    %h2.jq-clearfix.roundTop.section-title
      %span.name .removeAttr( attributeName )
      %span.returns
        Returns:
        %a.return{:href => "http://docs.jquery.com/Types#jQuery"} jQuery
    .entry-details
      %p.desc
        %strong> Description:
        Remove an attribute from each element in the set of matched elements.
      %ul.signatures
        %li#removeAttr-attributeName.signature
          %h4.name
            %span.versionAdded>
              version added:
              %a{:href => "/category/version/1.0/"} 1.0
            \.removeAttr( attributeName )
          %p.arguement
            %strong> attributeName
            An attribute to remove.
      .longdesc
        %p
          The
          %code .removeAttr()
          method uses the JavaScript
          %code removeAttribute()
          function, but it has the advantage of being able to be called directly on a jQuery object and it accounts for different attribute naming across browsers.
      %h3 Example:
      #entry-examples.entry-examples
        #example-0
          %h4
            %span.desc Clicking the button enables the input next to it.
          %pre
            %code.example.demo-code
              :preserve
                &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
                &lt;html&gt;
                &lt;head&gt;
                  &lt;script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/head&gt;
                &lt;body&gt;
                	&lt;button&gt;Enable&lt;/button&gt;
                &lt;input type="text" disabled="disabled" value="can't edit this" /&gt;
                &lt;script&gt;
                $("button").click(function () {
                  $(this).next().removeAttr("disabled")
                  .focus()
                  .val("editable now");
                });
                &lt;/script&gt;
                &lt;/body&gt;
                &lt;/html&gt;          %h4 Demo:
